g the best player on the opposing side.\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Through four games,Brooksfinished with averages of 11.3 points per game on 40.5 field goal percentage and 46.2 three-point percentage, 3.8 rebounds per game, 1.5 assists per game and 1.0 steals per game.\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The FIBA version of theOregon Duckis better than any other version of himself.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"score\": 0.9999790745884879, \"rank\": 2.0924283218582723e-05, \"text\": \"FIBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Canadians did end up coming out on top of Group A, or the \\\"Group of Death\\\", with Australia, Greece and Spain, by going 3-0 in pool play.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 895, \"end\": 902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EuroBasket_2009\", \"score\": 0.9999999999092779, \"rank\": 9.051264237227853e-11, \"text\": \"Group A\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EuroBasket_2009\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EuroBasket_2009\"}, {\"begin\": 934, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9980955244743415, \"rank\": 0.0015261603185983473, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9082372541535502, \"rank\": 0.09977116388534672, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.